ervlet, hibernate, terracotta, and size of the agent. They seem optional and aren't necessary for core in-process coverage. I shouldn't introduce an external Terracotta server unless the tests specifically aim at clustering. That makes sense; I want to keep the tests focused and avoid unnecessary complexity while staying efficient!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_08f50d2a49970e64016a42863c3ce88190b44ee95ce639e9c4\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQoZbV7qDNB3g273hxWwNcxIMeUjpYJAl4U0NNX4a7gre-RPl_F_Llslkgnt0o1h48dBtjRNqA7NEyHDVldvEDXnOTWCJhksNy-fsrdDf8QIPWplJ4BBZXVtKm94cX1rjFPlKUX_5xArzSrzuHFw1cqb6PKBTL9mhPky3zB0FaC8ZPWtV8sx8A1TpZhKtPbrxJGyT3yWspCfw_55Xq8jQgDzax3_5ebmY44c9TX2pKRqJEZfsurcUgbciehOwqBRbO1Tnu9KnoumY80xOM7FBUtaBcz72cw3UXqrEcKe3qnoDrba-5dgSORUOok9r7i9Fr-m_fA5EymC_MQEWH9soO8lCZgP_EhAgrE0_nwF0oJVfM53tqdqUs4aG0PaIg4pIUmYEuwj1xbOExuRGWMzLmQz7P8R0Yx-pU7nNVyN6khmD-3Zf1SLE_P_0vYyZucTpTvoMnTFABAU1yZIiwF1NDGxPZwei1qKBIpRbeg1Q-GiSeIkz-w13P67eIzXJjMNkKPUkQFfAmD6ygPuZ7WpHwk58FCaDSLQVbys4aS20auW2mPag0l6hHDhS-sDA0KG2a8nE2CsjqAexZ1qXxDj-WTUzBXTmAImCKRaxzARh0hOc6agsoLDbY4QaBvsLljSLLAxJkI9oVRSeVYo0L8PBKrD-IP3KkpPXZBda6_4KLJ-x76tM6nrRE5EUdTub7MfR6IdUUB-zkf01r-2saGyL3PeUd50yfTO8O9Vjvfnu3isUoSdOSDn1lWRW7Q5mvuv-VlggJxDy5QtWSbPSvHSJyE-svvvni6zhzCnvZnzNdppA3huiG_jI2NoxqmVxHQ5GIb6HBNLEjaImInaW26_oShF0W_qWrYVTVq6H2-lC-xMAs_rCltNveZ52kPvBYaBRSVGDm7_ro8v4qW2EYTrL-gfi2la9rwLAp1eB4MuBAXl1ZwjWH01ECTMh13ShdB_XSwvCDz4mXsT9B6FEKU2D_EMC4dpjoZA11uE9ohg3yFnzkJJTmt0Jwh_7FMVcfsHSfI1Tk9aPP7qgw2FobA8Fd9tyoXaZ7L2uTcJdvozAnHQVrqcdzqszn0yheCWPlGFaaKBJqJAgbcUmi9K9PbdEc3yT2Z8A3aAj9fUlO7ermW7qQX8hqlGhO9JFe3t9H80jtFgWPGWY6pc338fXbW5KH5s4hv6mMFIR7kELTme_CJkQ-Xt3h1_KUVP1wVHPb-WiS79zL2LqT0SVFfkYxqjWS6x2sbDPA_MxQUIPMu92zar4gHmhLFz1HYGLFvqDbymaWzqAeEyzheDciJYxGDy74j82Ln0rAcqIl3KDVK-NPEkQiZUmjuf7GQ28UwmYFu7MpTZf2oz1Ph1YTRpyK4njeH3aZSJVuiSHThg3WMgrhlTRisEUgtDZcVAjTSiHexvn9BuFwkqj5EZARe2D4t17spkEg72S8i7V8Xj4rvZIdBOVk-Q24g1cB29Wi2xP7vjih5QIarHsNcVXlYbhq-o4YPYXCpKvYDMnaM