m5ktC1Ph2A9LznTziG7bZZ4fyHOHlQsKtZgvtRVPoEkst3owTotrd2Ru92PH05KOr03r1MdMWfmwe12_3pQIhbLeRvcrJwLrJ9IvMBLveQ0Wyq6A0YcTF9T2bg=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing dependencies**\\n\\nI’m considering the effective versions of dependencies in relation to POM parent and possibly dependencyManagement. BTM has its dependencies, implying transitive inclusion, but including it brings in others like JTA and Geronimo. \\n\\nIf Ehcache imports javax.transaction in its public APIs, this might complicate test compilation. The setup could list both BTM and JTA deterministically, without needing Geronimo. I’m wondering if Docker could be necessary for a Terracotta server. Let's clarify these dependencies!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Ehcache integration**\\n\\nThe Ehcache documentation mentions clustering with Terracotta, but it seems I can parse the Terracotta config without needing a server. That could mean I don't need Docker after all! I might need to dive into the docs and Javadoc for citation support, but probably not in JSON.\\n\\nI should consider the risks here, like potential brittleness with transactions on older JTA versions and avoiding clustered tests needing an external server. It looks like there may be challenges with failing tests due to a possible Bitronix issue. I’ll need to clarify what additional setup is truly required.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining build setup**\\n\\nThe version 2.4.4 build is set with GVM_TCK_LV=2.5.0, and it seems I need to address potential metadata issues rather than setup. It feels like I should advise creating a deterministic setup for dependencies already listed in the build.gradle file.\\n\\nThe driver appears to start from version 2.4.4 tests with the existing build.gradle. It looks like the workflow for fixing “native-image run fails” just copies the current test project and updates the library version, so no additional setup is actually necessary since the dependencies are already in place.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Identifying integration risks**\\n\\nI need to consider the risks related to the provided scope integrations, like servlet, hibernate, terracotta, and size of the agent. They seem optional and aren't necessary for core in-process coverage. I shouldn't introduce an external Terracotta server unless the tests specifically aim at clustering. That makes sense; I want to keep the tests focused and avoid unnecessary complexity while staying efficient!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Ehcache Core has useful in-process cache coverage without external services, but meaningful coverage of its transaction/XA paths needs provided/test-only transaction infrastructure that the normal scaffold will not add.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.transaction:jta:1.1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"ehcache-core declares JTA as provided and its transaction APIs/classes reference javax.transaction types; tests that cover net.sf.ehcache.transaction.* need the API on the test classpath.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.codehaus.btm:btm:2.1.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"DefaultTransactionManagerLookup explicitly discovers Bitronix and the existing metadata covers bitronix.tm classes; adding BTM lets tests exercise the transaction-manager lookup and XA resource registration path.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.geronimo.specs:geronimo-jms_1.1_spec:1.1.1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Bitronix resource classes used for the Ehcache XA path reference JMS APIs; the existing Ehcache test scaffold pins this spec jar to keep that transaction setup resolvable.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Set System.setProperty(\\\"net.sf.ehcache.skipUpdateCheck\\\", \\\"true\\\") in tests that create CacheManager/configuration instances to avoid Ehcache's update-check network timer. For Bitronix coverage, create a temporary bitronix.properties file and set System.setProperty(\\\"bitronix.tm.configuration\\\", path) with disableJmx=true, journal=null, and a stable serverId; shut down TransactionManagerServices and clear the property after the test.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Terracotta clustered-cache features are optional integrations and would require external infrastructure; avoid them unless explicitly testing only local XML/config parsing.\",\n    \"Ehcache also has provided servlet, Hibernate, and sizeof-agent integrations, but those are not required for meaningful core cache/transaction coverage and should not be added without targeted tests.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_08f50d2a49970e64016a42865b44fc8190884608db2d9914fc\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4625, "output": 2037, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31750, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782744634905, "responseId": "resp_08f50d2a49970e64016a42863b67b08190a9954bba7aa6b162"}, "toolResults": []}
